sentences: Whyte was born in 1898 in Richmond, Kentucky.
This ensemble recorded for Gennett, Supertone, and Champion in 1929, amounting to about ten tunes.
Whyte died on March 10, 1967 in Kentucky.
Whyte's entire discography was reissued to CD on a Jazz Oracle compilation, Richmond Rarities 1927-31.
He led his own Cincinnati-based bands from the early 1920s, and put together the Chocolate Beau Brummels late in the decade.
